This tutorial demonstrates how to carry out parameter fitting of the central dogma transcription model 
The works on a 14.04 Linux of Google Compute Engine
Prerequisites: 
1. A working internet browser 

2. Esbalished Google Cloud Project with a Service Account Key associated with the Google Drive

In the home directory,
Installing Necessary packages thorugh pip:
1. If pip is not already installed, install pip by executing command "sudo apt-get install python-pip" in the home directory 

2. Install google's Python library to handle OAuth2.0 protocol. 
Execute the command "sudo pip install --upgrade oauth2client"

3. Install PyDrive, the wrapper library to handle interface with Google Drive API. 
Execute the command "sudo pip install PyDrive"

4. Install git. Execute the command "sudo apt-get -y install git"
 
5. Clone the git repository. Execute the command "git clone https://github.com/wollmanlab/akuma.git"

6. Follow and install and configure gcloud api 

7. copy the file client_secrets.json, which is associated with Google Service Account, into the local repository

8. cd into the local repository and execute the command to create 1 remote instance for data fitting. 
Execute the command "SubmitJobs.sh -f inputfile_centraldogma_tutorial -n 1 -i simIDListCentralDogma.p -d dataMatCentralDogma.p -s scoreThresholdListCentralDogma.p -x CentralDogma.xml -t timePointsCentralDogma.p -z us-west1-a"
